article.description: — Javon Levi had a triple-double with 14 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists to lead Texas-Arlington to an 83-73 win over Louisiana-Lafayette on Thursday night.
article.headline: Levi has triple-double; UTA beats Louisiana-Lafayette 83-73
article.linkText: Levi has triple-double; UTA beats Louisiana-Lafayette 83-73
article.story: ARLINGTON, Texas -- — Javon Levi had a triple-double with 14 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists to lead Texas-Arlington to an 83-73 win over Louisiana-Lafayette on Thursday night. Patrick Mwamba scored a career-high 22 points and had five assists for Texas-Arlington (8-8, 4-1 Sun Belt Conference), which earned its fifth straight home victory. Nicolas Elame added 13 points and six rebounds. Kaodirichi Akobundu-Ehiogu had three blocks. Kobe Julien tied a season high with 20 points for the Ragin' Cajuns (8-6, 3-1). Trajan Wesley added 13 points. Dou Gueye had 13 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
